Here's what's going to happen next on AS THE WORLD TURNS: 

Alison bonds with Will. Barbara lashes out at Hal.

Here's what just happened on AS THE WORLD TURNS: 

Carly is furious to learn that Craig lied to Rosanna that be 
slept with Carly before her wedding. When Carly lets slip 
that Rosanna is having a hysterectomy, a stunned Craig rushes 
to find her. Rosanna is relieved when a supportive Craig 
comforts her, vowing to see her through the surgery. Jack 
refuses to believe that JJ might not be his son. Carly 
chastises John for jumping the gun. Later, Carly reels when
John calls to inform her that JJ is definitely not Jack's 
son. Marshall awakens after his surgery and bonds with his 
father, while Ben releases Jessica from her promise to be 
with him if he saved Marshall. Sierra and Craig react when 
Ben tells them that Lucy is temporarily paralyzed Later, 
Sierra and Craig break the news to a devastated Lucy and 
explain Sierra's plan to take her to Montega. Lucy argues 
with Sierra about wanting to stay in Oakdale. Sierra blames 
Craig and goes to confront him but holds back when she 
overhears him at Rosanna's bedside following her surgery. 
Later, Sierra and Lucy have a tender rapprochement. 
Afterwards, Sierra and Craig are arguing when he realizes 
that she is jealous of his relationship with Rosanna. Lucy 
sees Alison wheeling a patient wearing a Washington 
University tee shirt. When the shirt triggers Lucy's memory, 
Alison rushes the patient out. Later, Lucy questions Alison 
about an argument she remembers them having in St. Louis.
Carly tells a guilt ridden Mike that he's off the hook with 
Rosanna since Craig lied that he was the one who slept with 
Carly before his wedding. When Mike tells Carly that Molly 
was asking about their relationship, Carly promises to clear
the air with Molly. Meanwhile, Molly learns that Rosanna is 
the mysterious buyer who purchased her penthouse. Jack 
struggles with the possibility that JJ may not be his son. 
Later, Carly and Jack go to the hospital for the results of 
JJ's paternity test, where Margo tells them that she may have 
found JJ's real parents. Aaron and Holden are thrilled when 
Hal surprises them with the news that all charges against 
Aaron have been dropped and apologizes for the trouble he 
put their family through. Later, Aaron works on a list, 
which he hopes will help Lucy regain her memory.

For the whole story of what happened last week, visit:
<a href="http://www.asthedialturns.com/astheworldturns.htm">
As The World Turns</a> 
http://www.asthedialturns.com/astheworldturns.htm

