Here's what's coming up next on GUIDING LIGHT: 

Tony turns his back on his old life and focuses on a future 
with Marah. A determined Olivia vows to repair her marriage. 

Here's what just happened on GUIDING LIGHT: 

Michelle is unhappy to learn that Rick and Ed had a discussion 
with Danny about her future. Mel encourages Michelle as she 
prepares for her New Year's Eve date with Danny. Later, 
Michelle opens the door to greet Danny but finds an escaped 
Carmen who has come with an agenda to kidnap Robbie. Cassie 
senses that Danny is nervous about his date with Michelle 
and offers to pretend to be her so that he can practice what 
he will say. Later, Cassie is moved to tears when Danny's 
words remind her of a similar New Year's Eve speech of 
Richard's. Phillip vows to help Olivia reconcile with Alan. 
Carmen pulls a gun on Michelle arid demands she hand Robbie 
over. When Michelle refuses, Carmen goes to shoot but Bill 
rushes in and tackles her, knocking her unconscious. After 
Carmen is taken to the hospital, Bill and Michelle end up in 
a kiss. Eden is stunned when Tony forgives her for killing 
his father. Tony tells Eden about the Santos family's new 
legit venture. Marah arrives and gets jealous when she hears 
Eden offering to work at Danny and Tony's new club. Later, 
Tony reassures Marah when she questions him about Eden.

Despite Prank's warnings, Harley goes to Roy Baker's apartment 
and is shocked to find Gus waiting for her. Harley comes 
clean about her investigation and tells Gus that Eden pushed 
Rico Santos off the roof after he revealed that their father 
was a dirty cop. An emotional Gus refuses to believe that his
father was on the take and Harley vows to help him prove his 
dad's innocence. Danny and Father Ray sit vigil with Carmen 
who remains in a coma. Danny is hopeful for a second chance 
after Michelle calls to see hint, but she tells him that she 
cannot get past the terror of New Year's Eve. Danny refuses 
to accept her decision and kisses her to prove their love. 
Beth is hurt and humiliated when Bill breaks up with her, 
acknowledging that she was right about his feelings for 
Michelle. Later, Bill goes to see Michelle and mistakes her 
kiss with Danny as reconciliation. A defeated Bill leaves 
without seeing her while Phillip comforts Beth.

For the whole story of what happened last week, visit:
<a href="http://www.asthedialturns.com/guidinglight.htm">
The Guiding Light</a>
http://www.asthedialturns.com/guidinglight.htm

